	<TraitDef>
		<defName>HMC_Lucks</defName>
		<commonality>1</commonality>
		<degreeDatas>
		  <li>
			<label>unlucky</label>
			<description>A hard life, numerous drinking bouts and countless twisted little fingers - {PAWN_nameDef} has a truly spectacular failure, as if the deities themselves had cursed {PAWN_gender ? him : her}.\nThis trait has truly miraculous properties to meet the player's expectations regardless of his faith, alignment, shoe size, favorite football club and the number of turtles in {PAWN_gender ? his : her} aquarium (especially if there are zero).\n\n    Luck -50%</description>
			<degree>-1</degree>
			<socialFightChanceFactor>1.5</socialFightChanceFactor>
			<commonality>0.5</commonality>
		  </li>
		  <li>
			<label>lucky</label>
			<description>With a carefree past, a fast-paced career and the pots of gold of numerous leprechauns – {PAWN_nameDef} has truly impressive luck, as if the deities themselves were blessing {PAWN_gender ? him : her} along the way.
\nThis trait has truly miraculous properties to meet the player’s expectations, regardless of his faith, alignment and number of turtles in {PAWN_gender ? his : her} aquarium (especially if there are not zero).
\n\n    Luck +50%</description>
			<degree>1</degree>
			<socialFightChanceFactor>0.5</socialFightChanceFactor>
			<commonality>0.5</commonality>
		  </li>    
		</degreeDatas>
	</TraitDef>

	<TraitDef>
		<defName>HMC_Conservatism</defName>
		<commonality>0.9</commonality>
		<degreeDatas>
		  <li>
			<label>conservatism</label>
			<description>“It was better before! We don’t need this communications console, pigeon mail is more reliable! Today’s Norbals are not at all the same, they are emaciated. But in our time...” – {PAWN_nameDef} does not trust any manifestations of novelty, preferring the old and proven time things, not forgetting to share your opinion with others.</description>
			<degree>-1</degree>
			<socialFightChanceFactor>1.25</socialFightChanceFactor>
			<statOffsets>
			  <MentalBreakThreshold>0.06</MentalBreakThreshold>
			  <GeneralLaborSpeed>0.2</GeneralLaborSpeed>
			  <GlobalLearningFactor>-0.15</GlobalLearningFactor>
			</statOffsets>
			<statFactors>
			  <CertaintyLossFactor MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Ideology">0.25</CertaintyLossFactor>
			  <SocialIdeoSpreadFrequencyFactor MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Ideology">2</SocialIdeoSpreadFrequencyFactor>
			</statFactors>
			<commonality>0.4</commonality>
		  </li>
		  <li>
			<label>cynicism</label>
			<description>{PAWN_nameDef} is disdainful of any dogmatic manifestations and {PAWN_possessive} does not care at all about the worldview of others. Without a twinge of conscience, {PAWN_gender ? he: she} will change his opinion to the dominant one in society in order to achieve his goals.</description>
			<degree>1</degree>
			<socialFightChanceFactor>1.12</socialFightChanceFactor>
			<statOffsets>
			  <MentalBreakThreshold>-0.04</MentalBreakThreshold>
			  <GeneralLaborSpeed>-0.05</GeneralLaborSpeed>
			  <GlobalLearningFactor>0.1</GlobalLearningFactor>
			</statOffsets>
			<statFactors>
			  <CertaintyLossFactor MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Ideology">4</CertaintyLossFactor>
			  <SocialIdeoSpreadFrequencyFactor MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Ideology">0.5</SocialIdeoSpreadFrequencyFactor>
			</statFactors>
			<commonality>0.5</commonality>
		  </li>    
		</degreeDatas>
		<conflictingTraits>
			<li>Religious</li>
			<li>Cultist</li>
			<li>Fanatic</li>
			<li>Naive</li>
		</conflictingTraits>
	</TraitDef>

